A \code{contam_tbl} is the canonical object returned by every tidypq contaminant
detector (\verb{identify_contam_*_pq()}). It is a tibble subclass with one row per
flagged taxon and at least two columns:
\describe{
\item{\code{taxon}}{Taxon name, matching \code{phyloseq::taxa_names()}.}
\item{\code{method}}{Short token naming the detector that flagged the taxon
(e.g. \code{"corr"}, \code{"blocklist"}, \code{"primer"}).}
}
Detectors add their own method-specific evidence columns (correlations,
p-values, matched primers, …). A detector that flags nothing returns a
zero-row \code{contam_tbl}, never \code{NULL}, so outputs always compose.

Outputs of several detectors can be row-bound with \code{\link[=rbind]{rbind()}}; evidence
columns absent from one detector are filled with \code{NA}. The combined table is
consumed by \code{\link[=filter_contam_pq]{filter_contam_pq()}} (removal) and by \code{\link[=plot.contam_tbl]{plot.contam_tbl()}}
(diagnostics).
